    "Let X ′ = {x ∈ X | ∃y ∈ Y: xR δ y}, so ∅ ̸ = X ′ ⊆ X.",
    "Now consider any Z ∈ ℘(W) \\ {∅} with X ′ R α Z, so Z ⊆ R α [X ′],and pick an x ∈ X ′ such that for some z ∈ Z, xR α z.",
    "Since x ∈ X ′, we also have a y ∈ Y with xR δ y.",
    "Then by (6.13), there is a u such that yR γ u and zR β u.",
    "Setting U = {u}, we have U ⊆ R γ [Y] and U ⊆ R β [Z], so Y R γ U and ZR β U."
